Week 7 of the prep football season in the Inland Northwest started, like usual, with a Greater Spokane League doubleheader. 
Rogers got things going with a 30-14 win over Shadle Park. The win continues a solid season for the Pirates, who are now 3-4. 
Mead had a tough draw to start GSL 4A play. The Panthers lost to first place Gonzaga Prep and Central Valley. Mead earned its first league victory, with a 45-7 win over Ferris. Read or Share this story: http://on.krem.com/1LwTLw9 TOP VIDEOS
